==English==

===Etymology 1===
{{etystub}}

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛld|-ɛld]]

====Alternative spellings====
*[[wold]]

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# {{botany}} A [[herb]] (''[[Reseda luteola]]'') related to [[mignonette]], growing in Europe, and to some extent in America; [[dyer's broom]]; [[dyer's rocket]]; [[dyer's weed]]; [[wild woad]].
# Coloring matter or dye extracted from this plant, used to give a yellow color.

===Etymology 2===
{{etystub}}

====Noun====
'''weld'''

# The state of being welded; the [[joint]] made by welding.

=====Derived terms=====
*[[butt weld]]
*[[scarf weld]]

====Verb====
{{en-verb}}

# {{transitive}} To [[bind]] pieces of [[metal]] together by [[melt]]ing the connection.
# {{transitive}} To bind together [[inseparably]]; to [[unite]] closely or [[intimately]].

=====Quotations=====
*'''1847''': [[w:Alfred Lord Tennyson|Alfred Lord Tennyson]], ''The Princess''
*: Now should men see / Two women faster '''welded''' in one love / Than pairs of wedlock.

